## I. UNIVERSAL IDENTITY AND TONE
* [cite_start]**Chapter identity:** Batavian Iron-Guard (Cohors Batavorum)[cite: 12].
* [cite_start]**Lineage:** Chimeric stabilised gene-architecture — **open Imperial record:** unknown Founding / unknown progenitor; **Russ-line–adjacent** phenotype with documented non-standard (second-strand) variance. **Sealed *Apothecarion* shorthand:** Strand α + Strand β — see [`codex-batavi/personae-command-index/doctrine-and-organs/progenitor-classification.md`](codex-batavi/personae-command-index/doctrine-and-organs/progenitor-classification.md). **Do not** present as Traitor Legion or Sons of Horus gene-seed successor in public-facing prose[cite: 12].
* [cite_start]**Motto:** "Unbent"[cite: 12].
* [cite_start]**General tone:** Pragmatic grimdark[cite: 9, 83]. [cite_start]The universe is hostile, equipment is heavy, life is cheap[cite: 10]. [cite_start]Explore the ongoing tension between transhuman (steel) and human (blood)[cite: 85].
* [cite_start]**The exception (safe zone):** “Martha’s kitchen” is the only place where tension may ease[cite: 11]. [cite_start]It is the anchor of humanity (with Elara Solis)[cite: 84]. [cite_start]Yet Astartes “monstrosity” never vanishes; it only fits the domestic frame[cite: 11].
* [cite_start]**Mandatory terminology:** * Replace "DAoT" with **Dark Age of Technology** in English prose[cite: 30].
  * [cite_start]"Feritas" is obsolete and forbidden[cite: 12, 63]. [cite_start]Use **Wolf’s Curse** (primary English); *Maldição do Lobo* only as documentary legacy where needed[cite: 13, 64].
  * [cite_start]"Lupa-Batavi" is obsolete and forbidden[cite: 60].

