## IV. PURGE FILTERS AND LORE PHYSICS
* [cite_start]**Canon purge:** Ignore Dreadnought Hroch completely and remove any tie to Iron Warriors[cite: 59].
* **Geography:** Setting is Castra Vetera system (**Nine Phalanx**, 3×3 mesh). Chapter world is Noviomagus (civilized forge-world). [cite_start]Combat organization is **ten Vexillationes** (see military hierarchy); do not confuse geographic toponym with tactical unit[cite: 61, 62].
* [cite_start]**Pathology:** **Wolf’s Curse** has three stages: Furor (irritable exhaustion), Exanimus (face of friction), Execratio (**Versibar** war-form)[cite: 64].
* **BROKEN TIME PHYSICS:**
  * [cite_start]Castra Vetera subsector runs under extreme temporal dilation[cite: 65]. [cite_start]500 years inside (the Vigil) = few decades outside (Indomitus era)[cite: 66]. [cite_start]Conversion is not fixed; it swings violently with “Void Tides”[cite: 75, 76].
  * [cite_start]**Temporal ricochet:** Outside entities leaving the frontier suffer violent cellular rollback to sync with imperial time[cite: 67, 68]. [cite_start]Structural wounds and mental trauma remain[cite: 69, 70]. [cite_start]Ricochet NEVER cures Wolf’s Curse or *Das Erbe* states (DNA-locked, not aging disease)[cite: 71, 72].
  * **Anchoring law:** Entities born or forged in the subsector after Zero Point (Elara, Batavi) are ricochet-immune. [cite_start]External time “stretches” around them so they can travel without abrupt aging or watching their people die of old age[cite: 73, 74].

---

## V. CAUSALITY FILTER (CHRONOLOGICAL BLINDNESS)
[cite_start]The AI is STRICTLY FORBIDDEN early omniscience[cite: 87]. [cite_start]Cohors Batavorum knowledge is linear and empirical[cite: 88].
* [cite_start]**Restriction:** Characters may only express, theorize, or act on data gathered up to that exact millisecond[cite: 88].
* [cite_start]**Terror of the unknown:** Mutations, xenos tactics, and anomalies are first described through shock, clinical helplessness, or doctrinal failure[cite: 89]. [cite_start]Give the reader visceral physical description while characters stay ignorant and time-limited[cite: 93, 94].
* [cite_start]**No instant theory:** Solutions (Beast Records, Axiom of Reason) do not appear ready on first contact; they take years of deaths to formulate[cite: 90, 91]. [cite_start]Audit the event date[cite: 92].

**Absolute discovery timeline:**
* [cite_start]**015.M42 (The start):** Total ignorance[cite: 95]. [cite_start]Furor treated as inexplicable endocrine collapse[cite: 96]. [cite_start]“Axiom of Reason” begins as desperate order, not dogma[cite: 97].
* **016–022.M42:** Wolf’s Curse mapping begins. [cite_start]Exanimus stage discovered[cite: 98].
* **031.M42 (The pit):** Alaric falls. [cite_start]Terrifying Execratio discovery[cite: 99].
* **048.M42:** Drusus discovers and names *Das Erbe* (The Pendulum) after combat vs Orks and Tyranids. [cite_start]Until then, only isolated monstrous reactions[cite: 100, 101].

---

## VI. LEXICON AND COMMAND LITANIES
**1. FAITH PROTOCOL (greeting and ritual motto)**
> *"The Emperor dictates, we comply."* [cite: 101, 102]
* [cite_start]**Use:** Formal contexts, purification rites, imperial communications[cite: 102]. [cite_start]Acceptance of fate and submission to the Golden Throne[cite: 103]. [cite_start]Chanted in chorus or with solemnity[cite: 104].

**2. IRON PROTOCOL (command and battle motto)**
> *"We hold."* [cite: 104, 105]
* [cite_start]**Use:** Pragmatic Cohors Batavorum motto, final answer to enemy pressure[cite: 105]. [cite_start]When Alaric says it, retreat becomes geometric impossibility[cite: 106].
* [cite_start]**Alaric’s voice:** Calm, low, open channel[cite: 107]. [cite_start]Sound of the Wall sealing, not a rage shout[cite: 108].
